# ── renv: local dev uses this, Docker bypasses it entirely ──
# .Rprofile sources renv/activate.R, which reconfigures .libPaths()
# to point ONLY at renv/library/ — hiding packages installed
# directly via install.packages() in the Dockerfile. Excluding
# these from the build context means R never sources renv at
# container startup; local development is completely unaffected
# since these files stay in the actual repo, just not copied here.
.Rprofile
renv/
renv.lock

# ── Secrets: Railway injects these as real env vars instead ──
.Renviron

# ── Never needed inside the container ────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
data/local_query_cache.duckdb
data/meds_raw/
data/temp_synth/
logs/*.md
notes/
docs/
*.Rproj
.Rproj.user